HEADWORD: Stinkstone
<hw>Stink"stone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>One of the varieties of calcite, barite, and feldspar, which emit a
fetid odor on being struck; -- called also
<altname>swinestone</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stinkweed</ent>⟦br⟧
